	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>TMS9918 clone</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Someone made a <a href="http://hardware.slashdot.org/story/12/02/11/2035226/tms9918a-retro-video-chip-reimplemented-in-fpga-with-vga-out" class="postlink">TMS9918 clone on an FPGA</a>. TMS9918 is the VDP in the ColecoVision, MSX, and TI-99/4A. The nearly pixel-perfect port of Donkey Kong to the ColecoVision <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5039" class="postlink">inspired</a> Nintendo to work on its own console. I wonder how hard it'd be to make an open source clone of the NES PPU and put it on opencores.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


